My dearest love, so sweet and bright,
I miss your laughter, pure and light.
Though sickness tries to steal your cheer,
Know that I am always near.

May warmth and rest bring you relief,
And chase away this fleeting grief.
Each moment spent away from you,
Feels gray and dull—so sad, so true.

But soon you’ll shine, so strong, so free,
And back to health, you’ll come to be.
Until that day, my heart will stay,
Right by your side, come what may.

So close your eyes and dream so sweet,
Let love and care your soul complete.
Get well, my love—please don’t forget,
I love you more than words have met.